{
  "stem": "13219.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Germans, when they finished killing all the Jews down there, they--",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Berezne.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They knew that there's a lot of hideouts which Jews hid.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the police were still there, the Jewish police.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So the second day they took out my mother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Somebody-- some Jewish guy, man, thought that if he's going to tell where my mother, my sister, whatever is, they'll spare his life.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they took out my mother with my sister, and when my mother went down the steps where she was coming, she knew where my brother was, and she says, [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What does that mean in English?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Be well, because I'm already gone.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that night, my brother, Julius, who is still alive, ran out in the middle of the night.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and he went the same path that I was going, and the same woman was there-- the same-- the third night.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she saw my brother walking-- we looked alike-- and she said, what's your name?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He said, I'm Julius Gershkowitz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So she said, I have one of your brothers here.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother was killed with my-- with my sister.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Taken to the graves there, and they shot her.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] I know because I've been told.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I know that my father was alive, and he was in the woods after-- about six or eight months after they killed.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He didn't know that we were alive, and one day, they-- he gave himself up.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because knowing that they killed his wife and the kids, he gave himself up.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, and they made him dig a grave, because the people told me about it-- were with him together-- are still in Israel now.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
